## Getting Started with Express

Express.js is a minimal and flexible Node.js web application framework that provides a robust set of features for web and mobile applications. Setting up a basic server is straightforward.

![Node.js and Express Logos](https://placehold.co/600x300.png)

### Basic Server Setup
Here's a simple example of an Express server:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World!');
});

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Example app listening at http://localhost:${port}`);
});
```

